<item>
            <title>[SEC-631] form-login page doesn&apos;t use spring messageSource for i18n translations</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-631</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using latest daily snapshot of spring-security with spring 2.5.1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;form-login page doesn&apos;t use spring messageSource for translations. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other jsp&apos;s get translated messages successfully, but my form-login page doesn&apos;t. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can get translations using &amp;lt;fmt:setBundle&amp;gt;, but then I don&apos;t get to use the nice stuff spring does.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
